//Fracture â€“ Proximal humerus - AO classifikation (AO11)

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Shoulder MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select 'Fracture' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Proximal humerus' radio button is enabled
And 'Clavicle' radio button is enabled
And 'Scapula' radio button is enabled
And 'Humeral diaphysis' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Proximal humerus' radio button
Then 'Mod. acc. to AO classifikation (AO11)' radio button is enabled
And 'Mod. acc. to Neer classification' radio button is enabled
And 'Serial number' input field is enabled
And 'Image number' input field is enabled
And 'Import reference image' image uploader field is enabled


When I select 'Mod. acc. to AO classifikation (AO11)' radio button
Then '11A: 2-part fracture, extraarticular' radio button is enabled
And '11B: Extraarticular, bifocal, 3-part fracture' radio button is enabled
And '11C: Intraarticular' radio button is enabled
And '11: Not further specified' radio button is enabled

When I select '11A: 2-part fracture, extraarticular'
Then 'Greater tubercle fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Lesser tubercle fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Surgical neck fracture' radio button is enabled

When I select '11B: Extraarticular, bifocal, 3-part fracture'
Then 'With greater tubercle fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'With lesser tubercle fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Other bifocal fracture' radio button is enabled

When I select '11C: Intraarticular'
Then 'Anatomical neck fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Anatomical neck fracture with greater tubercle avulsion' radio button is enabled
And 'Multifragmentary fracture' radio button is enabled

When I select '11: Not further specified'
Then 'Remodelling' radio button is enabled
And 'Suspected' radio button is enabled
